%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fnancy-buirski-dead-the-loving-story-1235709080%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fnancy-buirski-dead-the-loving-story-1235709080%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Chandrayaan-3's%20Success%2C%20A%20Look%20At%20India's%20Upcoming%20Space%20Missions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20set%20to%20launch%20its%20next%20space%20venture%2C%20a%20mission%20to%20study%20the%20sun%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20space%20weather%2C%20days%20after%20the%20historical%20landing%20of%20its%20Chandrayaan-3%20space%20craft%20on%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20highlights%20of%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation's%20(ISRO)%20upcoming%20and%20past%20missions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EADITYA-L1%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESlated%20for%20launch%20on%20Sept.%202%2C%20the%20Aditya%20L1%20(%20%26quot%3BAditya%26quot%3B%20is%20sun%20in%20Hindi)%20is%20the%20first%20Indian%20space%20mission%20to%20study%20the%20sun.%20The%20spacecraft%20will%20be%20placed%20in%20an%20orbit%20around%20the%20Lagrange%20point%201%20(L1)%20of%20the%20Sun-Earth%20system%2C%20about%201.5%20million%20km%20(930%2C000%20miles)%20from%20earth%2C%20where%20the%20gravitational%20effects%20of%20both%20bodies%20cancel%20each%20other%20out.%20That%20%26quot%3Bparking%20lot%26quot%3B%20in%20space%20allows%20objects%20to%20stay%20put%20because%20of%20balancing%20gravitational%20forces%2C%20reducing%20fuel%20consumption%20by%20the%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20aims%20to%20observe%20solar%20activities%20and%20their%20effects%20on%20space%20weather%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20government%20sanctioned%20the%20equivalent%20of%20about%20%2446%20million%20for%20the%20Aditya-L1%20mission.%20ISRO%20has%20not%20given%20an%20official%20update%20on%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGAGANYAAN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20first%20crewed%20space%20mission%20(%26quot%3BGagan%26quot%3B%20means%20sky%20in%20Hindi%2C%20%26quot%3Byaan%26quot%3B%20is%20craft)%20plans%20to%20launch%20a%20crew%20of%20three%20to%20an%20orbit%20of%20400%20km%20(250%20miles)%20for%20a%20three-day%20mission%20before%20landing%20in%20Indian%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20has%20said%20its%20Vikram%20Sarabhai%20Space%20Centre%20had%20successfully%20tested%20systems%20for%20stabilising%20the%20crew%20module%20and%20safely%20reducing%20its%20velocity%20during%20re-entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20deputy%20minister%20for%20science%20%26amp%3B%20technology%2C%20Jitendra%20Singh%2C%20said%20about%2090.23%20billion%20rupees%20(%241.08%20billion)%20had%20been%20allocated%20for%20the%20Gaganyaan%20program.%20ISRO%20says%20it%20will%20focus%20on%20achieving%20a%20sustained%20human%20presence%20in%20space%20once%20Gaganyaan%20is%20completed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20official%20kickoff%20date%20has%20been%20announced%2C%20but%20ISRO%20has%20said%20the%20mission%20will%20most%20likely%20be%20ready%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENASA-ISRO%20SAR%20(NISAR)%20SATELLITE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA-ISRO%20SAR%20(NISAR)%20is%20a%20low-Earth%20orbit%20observatory%20system%20jointly%20developed%20by%20NASA%20and%20ISRO.%20NISAR%20will%20map%20the%20entire%20planet%20once%20every%2012%20days%2C%20providing%20data%20for%20understanding%20changes%20in%20ecosystems%2C%20ice%20mass%2C%20vegetation%20biomass%2C%20sea%20level%20rise%2C%20ground%20water%20and%20natural%20hazards%20including%20earthquakes%2C%20tsunamis%2C%20volcanoes%20and%20landslides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoughly%20the%20size%20of%20an%20SUV%2C%20the%20satellite%20is%20set%20to%20be%20launched%20from%20India%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20next%20year%2C%20with%20a%20target%20launch%20set%20for%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPAST%20MISSIONS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandrayaan-3%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20On%20August%2023%2C%20India%20became%20the%20first%20country%20to%20safely%20land%20a%20craft%20in%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole%20region.%20The%20mission%20is%20ongoing%2C%20with%20ISRO%20saying%20its%20rover%20had%20confirmed%20the%20presence%20of%20sulphur%2C%20iron%2C%20oxygen%20and%20other%20elements%20on%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandrayaan-2%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%202019%2C%20ISRO%20launched%20its%20second%20moon%20mission%2C%20its%20first%20attempt%20to%20study%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole.%20The%20mission%20included%20an%20orbiter%2C%20lander%20and%20rover%2C%20and%20was%20launched%20amid%20high%20expectations.%20Although%20it%20deployed%20the%20orbiter%20successfully%2C%20the%20lander%20crashed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMars%20Orbiter%20Mission%20(MOM)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%202013%2C%20ISRO%20became%20the%20fourth%20space%20agency%20to%20put%20a%20spacecraft%20in%20the%20Mars%20orbit.%20MOM%2C%20which%20had%20a%20projected%20mission%20time%20of%20only%20six%20months%2C%20did%20not%20lose%20contact%20with%20ground%20controllers%20until%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandrayaan-1%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20India's%20first%20mission%20to%20the%20Moon%20was%20launched%20successfully%20in%202008.%20The%20satellite%20made%20more%20than%203%2C400%20orbits%20around%20the%20moon%20and%20confirmed%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20ice%20on%20the%20moon%3B%20the%20mission%20concluded%20when%20communication%20with%20the%20spacecraft%20was%20lost%20on%20Aug.%2029%2C%202009.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693452960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fegstk8uo_chandrayaan3_625x300_15_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%