0greater%20declines%20observed%20for%20females%20(by%205.2%25%20points%20compared%20to%201.5%25%20points%20decline%20for%20males).%20The%20decline%20in%20female%20participation%20in%20casual%20work%20cannot%20be%20justified%20with%20unavailability%20of%20work%20under%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(MGNREGA)%20since%20female%20participation%20in%20MGNREGA%20remains%20around%2055%25%20over%202018-19%20and%202021-22%20according%20to%20official%20statistics.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20industry%20wise%20participation%20confirms%20that%20their%20participation%20has%20largely%20fall%20in%20non-agricultural%20activities%20like%20in%20construction%20work%20it%20has%20reduced%20from%206%25%20to%205.3%25%2C%20in%20trade%2C%20hotel%20and%20restaurant%20from%204.3%25%20to%203.7%25%2C%20other%20service%20from%209.1%25%20to%206.8%25%20respectively.%20The%20increase%20in%20household%20chores%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20care%20responsibilities%2C%20competition%20from%20jobless%20males%2C%20and%20the%20pressure%20of%20reverse%20migration%20could%20have%20been%20other%20reasons%20for%20this%20decline.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20males%2C%20the%20industry-wise%20participation%20confirms%20that%20their%20participation%20decline%20is%20mainly%20visible%20in%20agriculture%2053.2%25%20to%2051%25%2C%20but%20increase%20in%20participation%20in%20all%20other%20non-agricultural%20sectors%20mentioned%20above.%20So%2C%20the%20rural%20dynamics%20is%20changing%20in%20post%20COVID%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20is%20clear%20that%20while%20females%20were%20systematically%20pushed%20out%20from%20all%20these%20non-agricultural%20activities%20and%20greater%20engagement%20with%20farming%2C%20males%20are%20more%20in%20wholesale%20and%20retail%20trade%2C%20construction%20work%2C%20manufacturing%2C%20transport%2C%20communication%2C%20and%20other%20services%20which%20were%20even%20if%20disrupted%20by%20pandemic-induced%20lockdown%20but%20males%20reestablish%20their%20foothold.%20Conversely%2C%20for%20females%2C%20the%20displacement%20appears%20to%20be%20enduring%20and%20irreversible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EComing%20to%20regular%20salaried%20jobs%2C%20workers%E2%80%99%20participation%20in%20them%20fell%20in%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20irrespective%20of%20gender%20because%20of%20the%20lockdown.%20However%2C%20the%20magnitude%20of%20decline%20was%20more%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20which%20have%20a%20higher%20concentration%20of%20regular%20salaried%20jobs.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20is%20noticeable%20that%20the%20magnitude%20of%20decline%20is%20more%20for%20females%20than%20males%20in%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20which%20again%20reenforces%20the%20notion%20of%20discouraged%20worker%20effect%20or%20permanent%20loss%20of%20women%20from%20job%20market.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20again%20can%20be%20connected%20with%20social%20security%20provision%20under%20regular%20jobs.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%202021-22%20PLFS%20report%2C%2062%25%20of%20regular%20salaried%20workers%20do%20not%20have%20a%20written%20job%20contract%2C%2049.2%25%20of%20regular%20wage%2Fsalaried%20employees%20not%20eligible%20for%20paid%20leave%2C%2053%25%20are%20not%20eligible%20for%20any%20social%20security%20benefit.%20The%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20exposed%20the%20fragility%20of%20livelihoods%20due%20to%20the%20growing%20informalisation%20of%20formal%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEducation%20and%20workforce%20participation%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20increase%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%20participation%20in%20rural%20areas%20was%20observed%20across%20all%20education%20levels%20after%20pandemic%20(Table%202).%20But%20the%20WPR%20was%20significantly%20higher%20for%20illiterate%20women%20and%20those%20who%20had%20studied%20to%20the%20primary%20level%2C%20coinciding%20with%20the%20higher%20participation%20of%20females%20as%20helpers.%20The%20U-shaped%20relationship%2C%20particularly%20the%20high%20WPR%20at%20low%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20was%20because%20those%20at%20the%20lower%20end%20of%20the%20education%20spectrum%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20remain%20unemployed.%20Interestingly%2C%20both%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%2C%20those%20with%20a%20technical%20education%20(diploma%2Fcertificate%20courses)%20obtained%20jobs%20at%20a%20greater%20proportion%20even%20after%20pandemic%2C%20which%20reconfirmed%20the%20importance%20of%20skilled%20workers%20to%20the%20service-led%20growth%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETable%202%3A%20WPR%20across%20education%20levels%20for%2015%20years%20above%20population%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20literate%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3ELiterate%2C%20up%20to%20primary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3EMiddle%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3ESecondary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3EHigher%20secondary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3EGraduate%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3EPost%20graduate%20and%20above%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3EDiploma%2F%20certificate%20courses%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20rowspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ERural%20female%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E2018-19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E30.7%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E29.8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E17.2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E13.8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E18.4%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E31.5%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E34.3%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd