ly%20be%20explained%20by%20the%20role%20of%20men%20as%20breadwinners%2C%20which%20was%20backed%20by%20a%20long%20history%20of%20masculinity.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20general%20perception%2C%20the%20higher%20workforce%20participation%20among%20less%20educated%20workers%20pointed%20to%20a%20precarious%20job%20recovery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20relatively%20lower%20workforce%20participation%20among%20the%20educated%20points%20to%20higher%20unemployment%20among%20the%20educated%2C%20perhaps%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20jobs%20that%20match%20their%20expectations.%20In%20all%20likelihood%2C%20technology-driven%20post-pandemic%20recovery%20may%20accentuate%20this%20problem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EImpact%20on%20the%20Disadvantaged%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20labour%20market%20is%20segmented%20among%20social%20and%20religious%20groups.%20Even%20though%20Covid-19%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20blind%20to%20social%20stratification%2C%20the%20vulnerability%20to%20the%20virus%20was%20not%20homogeneous%20in%20all%20social%20and%20religious%20groups.%20Overall%2C%20socially%20disadvantaged%20communities%20had%20a%20higher%20WPR%20than%20the%20general%20category%20and%20it%20increased%20after%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%93%20by%207.4%20percentage%20points%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20from%2040.6%25%20to%2048%25%2C%20followed%20by%204%20percentage%20points%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%2C%204.2%20percentage%20points%20for%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%2C%20and%203.4%20percentage%20points%20for%20the%20general%20category.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECompared%20urban%20areas%2C%20the%20work%20participation%20of%20women%20from%20disadvantaged%20communities%20was%20much%20higher%20in%20rural%20areas.%20After%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20was%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20female%20WPR%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20particularly%20among%20STs%20(from%2028%25%20to%2040.1%25)%2C%20followed%20by%20SCs%20(18.9%25%20to%2025.7%25)%20and%20OBCs%20(18.9%25%20to%2025.9%25).%20The%20male%20WPR%20has%20changed%20marginally%20by%203-4%20%25%20and%20remains%20around%2050-55%25%20across%20social%20groups%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas.%20Given%20the%20low%20asset%20base%20at%20home%2C%20perhaps%20women%20from%20disadvantaged%20social%20groups%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20wait%20for%20better%20prospects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20religion%2C%20Christians%20had%20the%20highest%20WPR%20(42.6%25)%2C%20followed%20by%20Hindus%20(40.5%20%25)%2C%20Sikhs%20(38.9%20%25)%2C%20and%20Muslims%20(33.5%25)%20in%202021-22.%20While%20there%20is%20no%20significant%20difference%20in%20the%20male%20WPR%20across%20religions%2C%20for%20females%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20it%20varied%20to%20a%20large%20extent.%20There%20was%20a%20notable%20surge%20of%209.4%20percentage%20points%20in%20the%20WPR%20within%20the%20Christian%20demographic%2C%20closely%20pursued%20by%20a%20rise%20of%205.7%20percentage%20points%20among%20Muslims%20and%20a%204.6%20percentage%20point%20upturn%20among%20Sikhs.Me%20Occupying%20the%20lower%20rung%20on%20the%20socio-economic%20hierarchy%2C%20individuals%20hailing%20from%20religious%20minority%20groups%20found%20themselves%20compelled%20to%20eschew%20unemployment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhether%20we%20look%20at%20the%20rise%20in%20unemployment%20or%20precarious%20employment%20after%20pandemic%2C%20it%20points%20to%20the%20sluggishness%20of%20the%20labour%20market.%20An%20examination%20of%20the%20latest%20PLFS%20shows%20that%20despite%20some%20improvements%20in%20labour%20market%20outcomes%2C%20concerns%20remain%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs.%20The%20analysis%20of%20labour%20market%20outcomes%20in%20terms%20of%20rural%20and%20urban%2C%20gender%2C%20education%2C%20and%20social%20and%20religious%20groups%20shows%20that%20structural%20questions%20relating%20to%20the%20segmentation%20of%20labour%20market%20require%20urgent%20attention.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20higher%20workforce%20participation%20among%20women%2C%20especially%20from%20disadvantaged%20groups.%20If%20these%20structural%20problems%20are%20not%20addressed%2C%20post-pandemic%20growth%20will%20be%20more%20unequally%20shared%20than%20earlier.%20Public%20policies%20designed%20to%20address%20concerns%20about%20the%20job%20market%20should%20not%20only%20focus%20on%20employment%20generation%2C%20which%20has%20been%20low%20since%20the%20pre-pandemic%20period%2C%20but%20also%20aim%20to%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENamrata%20Singha%20Roy%20teaches%20Economics%20at%20Department%20of%20Economics%2C%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693449016000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30181615%2F5319729242_621f1bdbd1_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findian-labour-market-inequality-quality-women%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20examination%20of%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%202021-22%20report%20shows%20that%20the%20sluggishness%20of%20the%20labour%20market%20continues%20and%20concerns%20remain%20about%20the%20quality%20of%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findian-labour-market-inequality-quality-women%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Projects%20worth%20Rs%2012%20trn%20planned%20under%20Gati%20Shakti%20initiative%3A%20Piyush%20Goyal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693448938000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F29%2Ffull%2F1693332036-9772.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fprojects-worth-rs-12-trn-planned