hird-largest%20economy%20buck%20the%20global%20slowdown%20that%20has%20left%20many%20major%20economies%2C%20including%20China%2C%20stuttering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES%26amp%3BP%20Global%20India%20services%20Purchasing%20Managers'%20Index%20has%20remained%20firmly%20above%20the%2050-mark%20separating%20growth%20from%20contraction%20for%20nearly%20two%20years%2C%20the%20longest%20stretch%20since%20August%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20growth%2C%20the%20central%20government%20has%20been%20front-loading%20its%20annual%20spending%20on%20infrastructure.%20In%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%20that%20started%20on%20April%201%2C%20India%20had%20spent%20nearly%2028%25%20of%20its%20capital%20expenditure%20budget%20of%2010%20trillion%20Indian%20rupees%20(%24120.91%20billion).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeutsche%20Bank's%20chief%20India%20economist%20Kaushik%20Das%20said%20a%203%25%20decline%20in%20wholesale%20prices%20will%20also%20contribute%20to%20the%20strong%20headline%20growth%20by%20reducing%20the%20%26quot%3BGDP%20deflator%26quot%3B%20used%20to%20calculate%20real%20economic%20growth%20by%20stripping%20out%20price%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMODERATION%20AHEAD%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomists%20say%20that%20price%20effect%20could%20reverse%20in%20coming%20months%2C%20and%20growth%20could%20cool%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20above%20average%20rainfall%20in%20July%2C%20August%20has%20been%20uncharacteristically%20arid%2C%20which%20pushed%20up%20prices%20of%20food%20staples%2C%20curtailing%20discretionary%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDry%20weather%20could%20also%20hit%20agriculture%20output%20and%20eat%20into%20power%20of%20the%20population%20in%20India's%20hinterlands%20where%20a%20majority%20depend%20on%20agricultural%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20slowing%20global%20growth%20and%20exports%20and%20a%20comparison%20with%20higher%20growth%20rates%20a%20year%20ago%20will%20also%20weigh%20on%20gr