usinesses%20are%20slowly%20becoming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-gptbot-crawler-major-companies-media-outlets-blocking-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaware%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20the%20web%20is%20being%20scraped%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20generative%20AI.%20The%20likes%20of%20Amazon%2C%20Airbnb%20and%20Tumblr%2C%20along%20with%20news%20outlets%20like%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20CNN%2C%20are%20increasingly%20blocking%20web%20crawlers%20through%20an%20old%20and%20relatively%20feeble%20tool%20known%20as%20robots.txt.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20there%20is%20almost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-killing-web-grand-bargain-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20way%20to%20avoid%20content%20being%20crawled%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20used%20to%20create%20an%20LLM%20and%20copyright%20law%20does%20not%20currently%20address%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Copyright%20Office%20noted%20that%20it%20has%20already%20ruled%20on%20a%20some%20AI-content%20issues%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20In%20one%20case%2C%20it%20refused%20to%20register%20a%20copyright%20for%20an%20AI%20generated%20artwork.%20In%20another%2C%20a%20book%20by%20a%20human%20author%20that%20included%20AI%20generated%20imagery%2C%20the%20Office%20only%20granted%20copyright%20for%20the%20text%20by%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Office%20is%20looking%20to%20go%20further.%20It%20wants%20to%20resolve%20several%20issues%20it%20has%20identified%20with%20regard%20to%20copyright%20and%20AI%2C%20including%20training%20data%2C%20whether%20AI%20generated%20material%20is%20eligible%20for%20copyright%2C%20liability%20for%20infringement%20by%20AI%20systems%20and%20how%20to%20treat%20AI%20outputs%20that%20%26quot%3Bimitate%20the%20identity%20or%20style%20of%20human%20artists.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20last%20issue%20appears%20to%20be%20new%20for%20the%20Office.%20Although%20th