-this-should-not-be-mistaken-for-people-power-12951053%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgabon-coup-this-should-not-be-mistaken-for-people-power-12951053%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgabon-coup-this-should-not-be-mistaken-for-people-power-12951053%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Data%20leverage'%20and%20the%20Harry%20Potter%20test%3A%20How%20much%20is%20a%20single%20book%20worth%20to%20a%20giant%20AI%20model%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22harry%20potter%20fans%20books%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5bdb2a3748eb123edf43fa92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20question%20of%20what%20data%20is%20used%20for%20AI%2C%20and%20the%20value%20of%20that%20content%2C%20is%20becoming%20a%20hot%20topic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECan%20you%20measure%20the%20value%20of%20a%20specific%20piece%20of%20data%20in%20a%20huge%20AI%20model%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20are%20trying%20to%20measure%20this%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0'data%20leverage'%20concept%20is%20gaining%20ground.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nick%20Vincent%20was%20studying%20how%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-is-changing-everything%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20relies%20on%20human-generated%20data.%20One%20thing%20always%20struck%20him%20about%20the%20researchers%20and%20tech%20companies%20behind%20these%20powerful%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20always%20highlight%20their%20clever%20algorithms%2C%20not%20the%20underlying%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vincent%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20computing%20science%20at%20Simon%20Fraser%20University%20near%20Vancouver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20beginning%20to%20change%20as%20the%20question%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-killing-web-grand-bargain-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20data%20is%20used%20for%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20value%20of%20that%20information%2C%20becomes%20a%20hot%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiant%20models%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gptbot-web-crawler-content-creators-ai-bots-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4-ai-model-got-lazier-dumber-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Google's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-how-big-tech-will-win-again-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaLM%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Meta's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-llama-2-data-train-ai-models-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELlama%202%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20been%20partly%20built%20on%20millions%20of%20books%2C%20articles%2C%20online%20chats%20and%20other%20content%20posted%20online.%20Some%20of%20the%20creators%20behind%20these%20works%20have%20sued%20claiming%20copyright%20violations%2C%20while%20others%20want%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20their%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20can%20you%20measure%20the%20value%20of%20a%20particular%20piece%20of%20data%20when%20a%20giant%20AI%20model%20has%20sucked%20up%20most%20of%20what's%20been%20published%20online%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20more%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20problem%20was%20highlighted%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ben-evans.com%2Fbenedictevans%2F2023%2F8%2F27%2Fgenerative-ai-ad-intellectual-property%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20AI%20by%20tech%20analyst%20Benedict%20Evans%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20need%20your%20book%20or%20website%20in%20particular%20and%20doesn't%20care%20what%20you%20in%20particular%20wrote%20about%2C%20but%20it%20does%20need%20'all'%20the%20books%20and%20'all'%20the%20websites.%20It%20would%20work%20if%20one%20company%20removed%20its%20content%2C%20but%20not%20if%20everyone%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVincent%2C%20the%20professor%2C%20calls%20this%20%26quot%3BData%20Leverage.%26quot%3B%20If%20communities%20better%20know%20the%20value%20of%20their%20data%20for%20AI%20models%2C%20they%20can%20more%20effectively%20negotiate%20payment%20for%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20know%20that%20all%20our%20books%20together%20are%20responsible%20for%20half%20the%20'goodness'%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20then%20we%20can%20put%20a%20value%20on%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20fringe%20concept%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20and%20it%20is%20becoming%20more%20mainstream%20now.%20I've%20been%20beating%20this%20drum%20for%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20finally%20happening.%20I'm%20shocked%20to%20see%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20makes%20LLMs%20tick%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20month%2C%20serious%20AI%20researchers%20waded%20into%20this%20debate%20with%202%20papers%20that%20seek%20to%20address%20various%20aspects%20of%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%207%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cofounder-artificial-intelligence-newsletter-import-ai-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most-advanced%20AI%20companies%2C%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2308.03296.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20describing%20a%20new%20way%20to%20more%20efficiently%20swap%20data%20in%20and%20out%2C%20and%20gauge%20how%20model%20performance%20changes.%20Until%20now%2C%20these%20types%20of%20tweaks%20to%20large%20language%20models%20have%20been%20so%20expensive%20they%20haven't%20really%20been%20tried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20an%20LLM%20outputs%20information%20it%20knows%20to%20be%20false%2C%20correctly%20solves%20math%20or%20programming%20problems%2C%20or%20begs%20the%20user%20not%20to%20shut%20it%20down%2C%20is%20it%20simply%20regurgitating%20(or%20splicing%20together)%20passages%20from%20the%20training%20set%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20combining%20its%20stored%20knowledge%20in%20creative%20ways%20and%20building%20on%20a%20detailed%20world%20model%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20Anthropic%20researchers%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20this%20work%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20a%20top-down%20approach%20to%20understanding%20what%20makes%20LLMs%20tick.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESILO%20and%20value%20of%20high-quality%20content%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%20up%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2308.04430.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESILO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20new%20language%20model%20developed%20by%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20in%20Seattle%2C%20UC%20Berkeley%2C%20and%20the%20Allen%20Institute%20for%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20broad%20goal%20was%20to%20create%20a%20model%20that%20can%20remove%20data%20to%20reduce%20legal%20risks.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20also%20developed%20a%20way%20to%20measure%20how%20specific%20data%20contributes%20to%20an%20AI%20model's%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSILO%20could%20provide%20a%20path%20forward%20for%20data%20owners%20to%20get%20properly%20credited%20(or%20be%20paid%20directly)%20every%20time%20their%20data%20in%20a%20datastore%20contributes%20to%20a%20prediction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20a%20paper%20unveiling%20the%20technology%20on%20August%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20settled%20one%20important%20question%20right%20away%3A%20AI%20models%20rely%20heavily%20on%20high-quality%20human-generated%20content%20that%20is%20often%20under%20copyright.%20Without%20that%2C%20performance%20begins%20to%20suck%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20show%2C%20model%20performance%20significantly%20degrades%20if%20trained%20only%20on%20low-risk%20text%20(e.g.%2C%20out-of-copyright%20books%20or%20government%20documents)%2C%20due%20to%20its%20limited%20size%20and%20domain%20coverage%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Harry%20Potter%20test%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20researchers%20went%20deep%20into%20the%20weeds%2C%20using%20J.K.%20Rowling's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenais-latest-chatgpt-version-hides-training-on-copyrighted-material-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarry%20Potter%3C%2Fa%3E%20books%20to%20see%20if%20individual%20pieces%20of%20data%20influence%20AI%20model%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20started%20with%20a%20large%20collection%20of%20published%20books%20that%20are%20part%20of%20The%20Pile%2C%20a%20huge%20dataset%20that's%20been%20built%20by%20scraping%20and%20storing%20a%20lot%20of%20what's%20been%20posted%20online%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20they%20created%202%20%26quot%3Bdatastores.%26quot%3B%20One%20had%20all%20the%20published%20books%2C%20except%20the%20first%20Harry%20Potter%20book.%20The%20other%20datastore%20excluded%20all%207%20Harry%20Potter%20books.%20They%20ran%20tests%20to%20see%20how%20the%20model%20performed%20with%20using%20those%202%20different%20datastores.%20Then%20they%20repeated%20the%20exercise%2C%20excluding%20the%20second%20Harry%20Potter%20book%2C%20then%20the%20third%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20idea%20with%20this%20%26quot%3Bleave-out%26quot%3B%20analysis%20was%20to%20see%20how%20well%20the%20model%20performed%20when%20these%20pieces%20of%20content%20are%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20Harry%20Potter%20books%20are%20removed%20from%20the%20datastore%2C%20the%20perplexity%20gets%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20found.%20Perplexity%20measures%20the%20accuracy%20of%20AI%20models.%20So%2C%20without%20Harry%20Potter%2C%20the%20model%20isn't%20as%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20specific%20conclusion%20seems%20painfully%20logical%2C%20but%20it%20is%20important%3A%20If%20you%20take%20specific%20content%20away%2C%20LLMs%20can't%20answer%20questions%20well%20about%20that%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLLMs%20threaten%20our%20ability%20to%20make%20these%20obvious%20conclusions%2C%26quot%3B%20Vincent%20said.%20%26quot%3BUntil%20now%2C%20throwing%20all%20data%20into%20an%20AI%20model%20has%20worked%20well.%20So%20there's%20been%20less%20need%20to%20specifically%20know%20what%20data%20is%20helping%20to%20make%20a%20model%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EImportant%20legal%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHelping%20J.K.%20Rowling%20make%20even%20more%20money%20from%20her%20Harry%20Potter%20books%20was%20not%20the%20goal%20of%20the%20SILO%20study%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20researchers%20proved%20is%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20build%20powerful%20AI%20models%20while%20mitigating%20legal%20risk%2C%20according%20to%20Oren%20Etzoni%2C%20former%20CEO%20of%20the%20Allen%20Institute%20for%20AI%20who%20remains%20a%20board%20member%20and%20advisor%20to%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20trained%20the%20SILO%20model%20only%20on%20low-risk%20datasets%20that%20contained%20public%20domain%20text%2C%20such%20as%20books%20where%20the%20copyright%20has%20expired.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20next%20step%20is%20called%20inference%2C%20where%20the%20model%20uses%20its%20training%20to%20interpret%20new%20information%20and%20decide%20the%20best%20output%20or%20course%20of%20action.%20The%20inference%20stage%20is%20where%20the%20researchers%20introduced%20the%20high-risk%20data%2C%20including%20those%20copyrighted%20books%2C%20along%20with%20news%20articles%2C%20medical%20text%2C%20and%20other%20content.%20This%20was%20where%20the%20Harry%20Potter%20%26quot%3Bleave-out%26quot%3B%20tests%20happened.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20has%20important%20legal%20benefits%2C%20according%20to%20Etzioni.%20Authors%20can%20opt%20out%20at%20any%20time%2C%20and%20the%20model%20does%20not%20have%20to%20be%20re-trained.%20In%20addition%2C%20particular%20sentences%20can%20be%20attributed%20in%20the%20results%2C%20enabling%20credit%20to%20be%20assigned%20to%20authors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20if%20authors%20insist%20on%20opting%20out%20en%20masse%2C%20then%20SILO%20will%20not%20end%20up%20being%20useful%20in%20practice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20is%20it%20legal%20to%20use%20copyrighted%20works%20at%20the%20inference%20stage%20of%20an%20AI%20model's%20development%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20question%20for%20a%20copyright%20attorney%2C%26quot%3B%20Etzioni%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-leverage-harry-potter-test-putting-value-data-ai-models-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693421311000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ee84bf96b7920019ca1b27%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-leverage-harry-potter-test-putting-value-data-ai-models-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20researchers%20are%20beginning%20to%20study%20the%20significance%20of%20human-generated%20data%20in%20AI%20models.%20This%20is%20taking%20the%20concept%20of%20'data%20leverage'%20more%20mainstream.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-leverage-harry-potter-test-putting-value-data-ai-models-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20100-year-old%20tree%20collapsed%20on%20the%20Florida%20governor's%20mansion%2