tps%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsoftbank-sells-1-16-stake-in-zomato-navi-mf-files-papers-with-sebi-123083001039_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Navi%20Mutual%20Fund%20may%20soon%20join%20other%20peers%20in%20launching%20a%20balanced%20advantage%20fund%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsoftbank-sells-1-16-stake-in-zomato-navi-mf-files-papers-with-sebi-123083001039_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsoftbank-sells-1-16-stake-in-zomato-navi-mf-files-papers-with-sebi-123083001039_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsoftbank-sells-1-16-stake-in-zomato-navi-mf-files-papers-with-sebi-123083001039_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indians%20Positive%20On%20Modi%2C%20Country's%20Influence.%20The%20Rest%20of%20the%20World%20Thinks%20Differently%3A%26nbsp%3BPew%26nbsp%3BReport%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24092024%2FFwz9N5AaEAYUoVS.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Almost%2070%25%20of%20Indians%20feel%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20the%20world%20is%20getting%20stronger%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Fviews-of-india-lean-positive-across-23-countries%2F%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20the%20think%20tank%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20a%20median%20of%2046%25%20of%20residents%20in%2023%20countries%20surveyed%20by%20Pew%20said%20that%20they%20had%20a%20favourable%20view%20of%20India.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20medians%20of%2034%25%20and%2016%25%20had%20unfavourable%20and%20no%20views%20on%20India%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20from%20a%20survey%20Pew%20conducted%20in%2019%20countries%20last%20year%20says%20that%20a%20median%20of%2028%25%20of%20people%20said%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20the%20world%20was%20getting%20stronger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20those%2019%20countries%2C%20respondents%20were%20most%20inclined%20to%20say%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20influence%20had%20not%20changed%20much%20in%20recent%20years%20(48%25%20median)%2C%20but%20only%2019%25%20of%20Indians%20agree%20with%20this%20view%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pew%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Fviews-of-india-lean-positive-across-23-countries%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_00-02%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_00-02.png%3Fw%3D528%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%20countries%20Pew%20conducted%20surveys%20in%20this%20year%2C%20respondents%20from%20Israel%20had%20the%20most%20positive%20views%20on%20India%2C%20with%2071%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20registering%20a%20favourable%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPew%20added%20that%20Israelis%20with%20right-wing%20political%20beliefs%20reported%20more%20positive%20views%20on%20India%20than%20Israelis%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20the%20spectrum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%2051%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20had%20a%20positive%20view%20on%20India.%20However%2C%20liberals%20were%2010%20percentage%20points%20more%20likely%20than%20their%20conservative%20counterparts%20to%20view%20India%20favourably.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Finternational-views-of-india-and-modi%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_01-02%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_01-02.png%3Fw%3D640%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20think%20tank%20has%20also%20found%20that%20while%20India%20is%20generally%20viewed%20favourably%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20including%20by%20residents%20of%20G20%20countries%2C%20delegations%20from%20which%20India%20will%20host%20next%20week%20in%20New%20Delhi%20%E2%80%93%20residents%20of%20some%20European%20countries%20and%20of%20South%20Africa%20see%20India%20less%20positively%20than%20they%20did%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAcross%20these%20select%20countries%2C%20views%20of%20India%20have%20generally%20become%20more%20negative%20since%20the%20question%20was%20last%20asked%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pew%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20observed%20the%20opposite%20phenomenon%20in%20Mexico%20and%20Nigeria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Finternational-views-of-india-and-modi%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_01-03%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_01-03.png%3Fw%3D640%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20viewed%20less%20favourably%20by%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20than%20India%20as%20a%20country.%3Cb%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22bold%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3EA%20median%20of%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20that%20they%20did%20not%20have%20confidence%20in%20Modi%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20regarding%20world%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPew%20did%20not%20ask%20European%20respondents%20about%20their%20confidence%20in%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20respondents%2C%20though%2C%20feel%20very%20confidently%20about%20their%20prime%20minister.%20Seventy-nine%20percent%20of%20Indians%20who%20were%20polled%20by%20Pew%20on%20their%20opinion%20of%20Modi%20reported%20a%20favourable%20view%2C%20with%2055%25%20of%20all%20Indians%20saying%20they%20had%20a%20%E2%80%98very%20favourable%E2%80%99%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2020%25%20of%20Indian%20respondents%20had%20an%20overall%20unfavourable%20view%20of%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Finternational-views-of-india-and-modi%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_01-04%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_01-04.png%3Fw%3D640%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Findians-views-of-modi-and-other-national-leaders%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_02-01%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_02-01.png%3Fw%3D640%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPew%20said%20that%20young%20adults%20from%20India%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20older%20respondents%20to%20answer%20its%20questions%20on%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20and%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20along%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20do%20not%20command%20%E2%80%98very%20favourable%E2%80%99%20views%20as%20the%20prime%20minister%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20regarding%20Indian%20respondents%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20also%20found%20that%20men%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20their%20female%20counterparts%20to%20believe%20that%20India%20was%20becoming%20a%20stronger%20force%20in%20the%20world%2C%20although%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20two%20in%20terms%20of%20percentage%20points%20(71%25%20and%2065%25%20respectively)%20is%20not%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Findians-views-of-india%2Fpg_2023-08-29_views-of-india_03-01%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2023%2F08%2FPG_2023.08.29_views-of-india_03-01.png%3Fw%3D640%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirty%20thousand%20people%20across%2024%20countries%20took%20part%20in%20Pew%E2%80%99s%20latest%20survey%2C%20which%20was%20conducted%20between%20February%20and%20March%20this%20year%2C%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findia-viewed-favourably-most-g20-members-modis-image-divided-survey-2023-08-29%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693409518000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F24092024%2FFwz9N5AaEAYUoVS.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpew-research-finds-indians-more-confident-of-country-than-rest-of-world%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%2079%25%20of%20Indians%20feel%20favourably%20about%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20a%20median%20of%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20from%2019%20countries%20other%20than%20India%20do%20not%20have%20confidence%20in%20Modi's%20foreign%20policy%2C%20finds%20a%20Pew%20survey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpew-research-finds-indians-more-confident-of-country-than-rest-of-world%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Laws%20Expand%20Their%20Reach%20in%20India%2C%20Political%20Freedoms%20Shrink%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30155424%2FScreenshot-2023-08-30-at-3.53.36-PM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20bills%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fthe-bills-in-perspective-8888597%2F%5C%22%3Etabled%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20in%20August%2C%20part%20of%20an%20overhaul%20of%20the%20entire%20criminal%20justice%20system.%20In%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20legacy%20of%20colonial%20law%2C%20they%20claim%20to%20replace%20%E2%80%98justice%E2%80%99%20with%20%E2%80%98punishment%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20aim%20and%20put%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20substantive%20criminal%20law%20in%20India%20has%20long%20been%20governed%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F4219%2F1%2FTHE-INDIAN-PENAL-CODE-1860.pdf%5C%22%3EIndian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20of%201860%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20colonial%20era.%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-bharatiya-nyaya-sanhita-2023%5C%22%3EBill%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20replace%20the%20IPC%20features%20175%20amended%20sections%2C%20eight%20new%20additions%20and%20the%20repeal%20of%2022%20sections%2C%20including%20the%20section%20on%20sedition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20legislation%20raises%20questions%20about%20whether%20colonial%20laws%20alone%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20shrinking%20of%20democratic%20freedoms%20in%20India%2C%20and%20whether%20new%20laws%20can%20restore%20fundamental%20freedoms%20of%20speech%2C%20association%20and%20dissent%20to%20the%20citizenry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20of%20democratic%20freedoms%20in%20India%20can%20be%20assessed%20in%20three%20ways%3A%20comparing%20the%20space%20for%20civil%20liberties%20in%20colonial%20and%20post-colonial%20laws%20restricting%20fundamental%20freedoms%2C%20analysing%20how%20these%20laws%20have%20been%20implemented%2C%20and%20assessing%20the%20democratic%20rights%20afforded%20by%20the%20proposed%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20justification%20for%20laws%20restricting%20freedoms%20relates%20to%20concerns%20around%20public%20order%20and%20national%20security%2C%20but%20patterns%20of%20implementation%20suggest%20the%20possibility%20of%20their%20political%20use%20against%20dissident%20voices.%20This%20blurs%20the%20boundary%20between%20criminal%20offence%20and%20legitimate%20dissent%2C%20rendering%20dissenters%20as%20criminals.%20Only%20those%20laws%20and%20regulations%20with%20a%20tightly%20defined%20scope%20of%20criminality%20will%20pass%20the%20test%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDissent%20in%20India%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20guaranteed%20as%20part%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1218090%2F%5C%22%3EArticle%2019%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20rights%20to%20speech%20and%20to%20peaceful%20assembly%20and%20association%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20imposes%20reasonable%20restrictions%20on%20the%20exercise%20of%20these%20rights%20in%20the%20name%20of%20protecting%20certain%20identified%20interests%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98public%20order%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98security%20of%20state%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20restrictions%20mark%20the%20threshold%20between%20legitimate%20dissent%20and%20criminal%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20action%20is%20perceived%20to%20be%20criminal%2C%20a%20charge%20is%20filed%20against%20them%20under%20a%20specific%20law.%20The%20adjudication%20process%20involves%20the%20judiciary%20deciding%20whether%20a%20citizen%E2%80%99s%20exercise%20of%20their%20freedom%20exceeds%20constitutional%20restrictions%20and%20whether%20the%20curtailment%20of%20liberty%20through%20the%20invocation%20of%20specific%20laws%20is%20reasonable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20the%20determination%20is%20on%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20laws%20in%20restricting%20freedoms%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20right%20to%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECriminalising%20dissent%20and%20disaffection%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20colonial-era%20law%20which%20comes%20into%20conflict%20most%20obtrusively%20with%20the%20right%20to%20speech%20is%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1641007%2F%5C%22%3Elaw%20against%20sedition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20enacted%20in%201870%20(Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20used%20by%20all%20successive%20governments%20post-independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20original%20form%2C%20which%20still%20stands%20in%20the%20penal%20code%2C%20the%20law%20criminalises%20all%20forms%20of%20expression%20which%20incite%20%E2%80%98hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%E2%80%99%20against%20the%20government.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20in%201962%2C%20however%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F111867%2F%5C%22%3Einterpreted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0it%20to%20apply%20only%20to%20those%20that%20incite%20disorder%20or%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20latest%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FCII-2021%2FCII_2021Volume%25202.pdf%5C%22%3Eofficial%20figures%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%202021%2C%2076%20initial%20police%20reports%20for%20sedition%20were%20registered%20across%20India.%20In%20May%202022%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F134384639%2F%5C%22%3Elaw%20was%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20re-examination%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20its%20glaring%20misuse%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%5C%22%3EHow%20Consultative%20Was%20the%20Framing%20of%20the%20Three%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%2C%20Really%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20laws%20enacted%20after%20independence%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FA1967-37.pdf%5C%22%3EUAPA%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20also%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20political%20freedoms.%20The%20UAPA%20was%20enacted%20in%201967%20but%20was%20given%20its%20contemporary%20form%20through%20subsequent%20amendments%20carried%20out%20in%202004%20and%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20an%20extraordinary%20law%20%E2%80%93%20meaning%20that%20it%20makes%20exceptions%20to%20the%20usual%20safeguards%20provided%20to%20an%20accused%20and%20lays%20out%20special%20conditions%20with%20regard%20to%20bail%2C%20investigation%20and%20trial.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20UAPA%20criminalises%20acts%20and%20expressions%20which%20%E2%80%98disrupt%20the%20territorial%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%99cause%20disaffection%20against%20India%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAPA%20also%20has%20provisions%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2Fen%2Fbanned-organisations%5C%22%3Ebanning%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20criminalising%20association%20with%20banned%20organisations.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2012%2F38%2Fcommentary%2Fcriminalising-dissent.html%5C%22%3Efar-reaching%20consequences%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20exercise%20of%20all%20possible%20fundamental%20freedoms%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMisusing%20the%20law%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnnual%20crime%20statistics%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fen%2Fcrime-in-india%5C%22%3Ereveal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20both%20a%20colonial-era%20laws%20like%20sedition%20and%20post-colonial%20legislation%20like%20the%20UAPA%20are%20being%20used%20with%20equal%20readiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20use%20is%20marked%20by%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20cases%20and%20an%20abysmally%20poor%20rate%20of%20conviction.%20The%20ratio%20makes%20clear%20that%20the%20laws%20have%20been%20misapplied%20in%20an%20overwhelming%20number%20of%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20363%20cases%20registered%20under%20the%20sedition%20law%20between%202017%20and%202021.%20The%20number%20of%20convictions%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20is%20only%20six%2C%20against%2051%20cases%20of%20acquittal.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20cases%20remain%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FCII-2021%2FCII_2021Volume%25202.pdf%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0alone%2C%20the%20pendency%20rate%20%E2%80%93%20cases%20awaiting%20settlement%20%E2%80%93%20was%2096.9%20percent.%20Cases%20registered%20under%20sedition%20law%20have%20included%20instances%20of%20cheering%20for%20a%20rival%20cricket%20team%2C%20offensive%20social%20media%20posts%2C%20WhatsApp%20message%20forwards%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-sufficient-ground-to-invoke-sedition-against-ranas-court-on-hanuman-chalisa-case%5C%22%3Erecital%20of%20Hanuman%20Chalisa%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20others%2C%20with%20no%20inherent%20element%20of%20incitement%20to%20violence.%20These%20facts%20were%20acknowledged%20by%20the%20court%20while%20suspending%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20800%20cases%20of%20sedition%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsedition.article-14.com%2F%5C%22%3Ewere%20filed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0between%202010%20and%202021%20against%2013%2C000%20people.%20There%20was%20a%2028%20percent%20annual%20rise%20in%20cases%20after%202014%2C%20when%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fen%2Fcrime-in-india%5C%22%3Eannual%20crime%20statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%204%2C919%20cases%20were%20registered%20under%20the%20UAPA%20between%202017%20and%202021.%20The%20average%20conviction%20rate%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20stands%20at%20around%2030%20percent%2C%20but%20this%20is%20based%20on%20a%20miniscule%20figure%20%E2%80%93%2095%20percent%20of%20cases%20are%20waiting%20for%20trial%20to%20be%20completed.%20Around%201%2C621%20people%20were%20arrested%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20one%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpucl.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FPUCL-28.09.2022.pdf%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%202.8%20percent%20of%20arrests%20made%20between%202015%20and%202020%20resulted%20in%20conviction%20under%20the%20UAPA.%20Despite%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Farticle%2F972-uapa-accused-jailed-long-periods-and-eventually-acquitted-study-finds-168494%5C%22%3Ethe%20poor%20conviction%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20accused%20end%20up%20suffering%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1010530%2Fin-seven-years-10552-indians-have-been-arrested-under-uapa-and-253-convicted%5C%22%3Elong%20periods%20of%20incarceration%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0because%20the%20UAPA%20sets%20conditions%20that%20make%20bail%20extremely%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20showed%20that%20out%20of%204%2C690%20persons%20arrested%20between%202018%20and%202020%2C%20only%201%2C080%20secured%20bail.%20Despite%20being%20a%20serious%20law%20invoked%20to%20counter%20threats%20to%20national%20security%2C%20it%20has%20been%20routinely%20used%20against%20students%2C%20journalists%2C%20human%20rights%20activists%20and%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkashmir-students-college-management-charged-with-uapa-for-celebrating-pakistans-win%5C%22%3Ecases%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0unrelated%20to%20national%20security%2C%20with%20inordinate%20delays%20by%20investigating%20agencies%20in%20completing%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20laws%20with%20broader%20reach%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20foremost%20issues%20with%20these%20laws%20is%20the%20ambiguity%20of%20their%20language%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98disaffection%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20which%20allows%20for%20all%20kinds%20of%20activities%20to%20be%20included%20in%20their%20scope.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20tabled%20in%20the%20Parliament%20in%20August%20cannot%20be%20seen%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20trend%20of%20overbroad%20and%20ambiguous%20legislation.%20It%20only%20replaces%20sedition%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.article-14.com%2Fpost%2Fhome-minister-amit-shah-says-sedition-is-dead-but-its-replacement-is-more-fearsome-than-the-colonial-law-ever-was-64d99ff8dc0d8%5C%22%3Eanother%20section%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20criminalises%20acts%20and%20expressions%20endangering%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20broadens%20its%20reach%20by%20removing%20the%20requirement%20of%20incitement%20of%20violence%20as%20a%20necessary%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20adds%20a%20new%20section%20on%20Offence%20of%20Terrorist%20Act%20(S.%20111)%2C%20which%20criminalises%20acts%20of%20provocation%20and%20intimidation%20likely%20to%20endanger%20public%20safety.%20The%20offences%20under%20UAPA%20are%20reproduced%20in%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20with%20no%20linguistic%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProvisions%20which%20may%20come%20into%20conflict%20with%20political%20freedoms%20are%20effectively%20retained%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20enhanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAnushka%20Singh%20teaches%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20Governance%20and%20Citizenship%2C%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20University%20Delhi%20(AUD)%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20India%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.oup.com%2Fproduct%2Fsedition-in-liberal-democracies-9780199481699%3Fsearchbox_input%3Danushka%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ESedition%20in%20Liberal%20Democracies%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F