20fact%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20official%20political%20map%20displayed%20Indian%20territories%20as%20within%20China%E2%80%99s%20borders%2C%20China%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20August%2030%2C%20dismissed%20the%20objection%20by%20describing%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20exercise%20of%20sovereignty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20advised%20New%20Delhi%20%E2%80%93%20without%20naming%20it%20%E2%80%93%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20over-interpret%E2%80%9D%20the%20action.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Monday%20night%2C%20Chinese%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20issued%20the%202023%20edition%20of%20standard%20map%20of%20China%20that%20continued%20to%20show%20the%20whole%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20the%20Aksai%20Chin%20region%20as%20part%20of%20its%20territory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20opposition%20party%20Congress%20creating%20a%20furore%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20termed%20those%20%E2%80%9Cabsurd%20claims%E2%80%9D.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20declaring%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnew-china-map-continues-to-show-whole-of-arunachal-pradesh-as-part-of-china%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estrong%20protest%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20was%20lodged%20with%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Wang%20Wenbin%20said%20the%20release%20of%20the%20standard%20map%20was%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20routine%20exercise%20of%20sovereignty%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law%E2%80%9D.%20Without%20taking%20India%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20that%20relevant%20parties%20will%20view%20it%20objectively%20and%20calmly%20and%20not%20over-interpret%20it%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20a%20machine%20translation%20of%20his%20response%20in%20Chinese%20during%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Ffyrbt_673021%2F202308%2Ft20230830_11135654.shtml%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edaily%20media%20briefing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20escalated%20its%20attack%20on%20the%20government%20of%20soft-pedalling%20on%20China%2C%20with%20party%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20urging%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20topic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20map%20issue%20is%20very%20serious%20but%20they%20have%20already%20taken%20away%20our%20land%20and%20the%20PM%20should%20say%20something%20about%20that%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20Congress%20president%20told%20reporters%20before%20he%20left%20for%20Karnataka%20earlier%20in%20the%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGandhi%20also%20repeated%20his%20previous%20line%20of%20attack%20that%20China%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20grab%20land%20during%20the%20current%20stand-off%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20just%20returned%20from%20Ladakh%20and%20I%20have%20been%20saying%20for%20years%20that%20what%20the%20PM%20has%20said%2C%20that%20not%20one%20inch%20of%20land%20has%20been%20lost%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20is%20an%20absolute%20lie.%20The%20whole%20of%20Ladakh%20knows%20that%20China%20has%20usurped%20our%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20foreign%20minister%20had%20previously%20defended%20against%20the%20opposition%20by%20claiming%20that%20stand-off%20was%20not%20over%20land%20grab%2C%20but%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fon-china-jaishankar-says-dispute-is-over-forward-deployment-not-about-land-grab%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforward%20deployment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20troops.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIssuing%20the%20statement%20about%20the%20protest%2C%20MEA%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reject%20these%20claims%20as%20they%20have%20no%20basis.%20Such%20steps%20by%20the%20Chinese%20side%20only%20complicate%20the%20resolution%20of%20the%20boundary%20question.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20today%20lodged%20a%20strong%20protest%20through%20diplomatic%20channels%20with%20the%20Chinese%20side%20on%20the%20so-called%202023%20%E2%80%98standard%20map%E2%80%99%20of%20China%20that%20lays%20claim%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20territory%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi.%20He%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reject%20these%20claims%20as%20they%20have%20no%20basis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20action%20came%20just%20a%20few%20days%20after%20a%20recent%20interaction%20between%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20during%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edisparate%20accounts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20two%20sides%20about%20the%20conversation%20concerning%20the%20border%20stand-off%20underscored%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20common%20understanding%20on%20de-escalation%20and%20disengagement%20on%20all%20the%20remaining%20friction%20points.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping%20is%20also%20scheduled%20to%20attend%20the%20G-20%20summit%20in%20India%20in%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%2C%20even%20though%20there%20has%20been%20no%20official%20announcement%20so%20far.%20It%20would%20be%20the%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20by%20the%20Chinese%20leader%20since%20October%202019%20for%20the%20second%20unofficial%20summit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693400113000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thew