d%20regions%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20this%20region%2C%20encompassing%20seven%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20including%20Bihar%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20West%20Bengal%2C%20bears%20the%20highest%20health%20burden%20attributable%20to%20particulate%20pollution%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20mentioned%20that%20the%20Northern%20Plains%20of%20India%20are%20synonymous%20with%20North%20India%2C%20Northern%20India%2C%20and%20the%20North%20Indian%20Belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faqli.epic.uchicago.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FAQLI_2023_Report-Global_Embargoed.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98AQLI%202023%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20written%20by%20Michael%20Greenstone%20and%20Christa%20Hasenkopf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFine%20particulate%20air%20pollution%2C%20known%20as%20PM2.5%2C%20has%20been%20found%20to%20reduce%20the%20average%20life%20expectancy%20of%20an%20Indian%20citizen%20by%205.3%20years%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%E2%80%99s%20(WHO)%20recommended%20guideline%20of%205%20%C2%B5g%2Fm3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20North%20India%2C%20this%20particulate%20pollution%20is%20even%20more%20severe%2C%20cutting%20lives%20short%20by%20eight%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20of%20the%20Northern%20Plains%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20a%20population%20of%20521.2%20million%20people%2C%20or%2038.9%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20population%2C%20reside%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20annual%20average%20particulate%20pollution%20levels%20are%2017.3%20times%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShockingly%2C%20from%201998%20to%202021%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20particulate%20pollution%20has%20surged%20by%2061%25%2C%20further%20diminishing%20life%20expectancy%20by%203.2%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20most%20polluted%20region%20of%20the%20Northern%20Plains%2C%20namely%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%2C%20its%2018%20million%20inhabitants%20are%20facing%20a%20potential%20loss%20of%2011.9%20years%20of%20life%20expectancy%20relative%20to%20the%20WHO%20guideline%2C%20and%208.5%20years%20relative%20to%20the%20national%20guideline%2C%20should%20current%20pollution%20levels%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-india-pollution-idUSKCN1QM1FH%5C%22%3Eranks%20as%20the%20most%20polluted%20city%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20and%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20following%20Diwali%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Femergency-think-of-urgent-steps-like-2-day-lockdown-sc-tells-centre-on-delhi-air-pollution%5C%22%3Esurge%20in%20cases%20of%20respiratory%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20health%20emergencies%20is%20reported%2C%20largely%20attributed%20to%20the%20significant%20increase%20in%20pollution%20resulting%20from%20the%20burning%20of%20firecrackers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20causes%20of%20air%20pollution%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-46138064%5C%22%3Ecan%20be%20attributed%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20burning%20of%20farm%20stubble%20in%20neighbouring%20states%2C%20industrial%20emissions%2C%20pollution%20from%20vehicles%2C%20and%20seasonal%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Chicago%20report%20further%20pointed%20out%20that%20even%20in%20the%20least%20contaminated%20district%20within%20the%20region%2C%20Pathankot%2C%20which%20is%20in%20Punjab%2C%20particulate%20pollution%20levels%20exceed%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20by%20more%20than%20sevenfold%2C%20thereby%20shortening%20life%20expectancy%20by%203.1%20years%20if%20current%20levels%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20India%20initiated%20the%20National%20Clean%20Air%20Programme%20(NCAP)%20as%20part%20of%20its%20%E2%80%9Cwar%20against%20pollution%E2%80%9D.%20Initially%2C%20NCAP%20aimed%20to%20decrease%20particulate%20pollution%20by%2020-30%25%20nationwide%20by%202024%2C%20focusing%20on%20102%20cities%20failing%20to%20meet%20India%E2%80%99s%20PM2.5%20standards.%20However%2C%20in%202022%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fnational-clean-air-programme-centre-aims-at-40-reduction-in-particulate-matter-by-2026%2Farticle65941247.ece%5C%22%3Erevised%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20pollution%20reduction%20target%20under%20NCAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20set%20a%20national%20goal%2C%20but%20instead%2C%20it%20set%20an%20ambitious%20city-level%20target%20of%20a%2040%25%20reduction%20by%202025-26%20for%20an%20expanded%20list%20of%20131%20non-attainment%20cities%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchieving%20this%20target%20would%20lead%20to%20a%2021.9%20%C2%B5g%2Fm%C2%B3%20reduction%20in%20annual%20average%20PM2.5%20exposure%20relative%20to%202017%20levels%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%202.1-year%20increase%20in%20life%20expectancy%20for%20citizens%20in%20these%20131%20cities%2C%20and%20a%207.9-month%20increase%20for%20the%20average%20Indian%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BAt%20least%5D%2038%20of%20these%20131%20targeted%20cities%20(almost%2030%25)%20belong%20to%20the%20Northern%20Plains%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693398546000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01140646%2F2019_10img31_Oct_2019_PTI10_31_2019_000257B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fworld-most-polluted-regions-north-india-delhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fine%20particulate%20air%20pollution%20lowers%20the%20average%20life%20expectancy%20of%20an%20Indian%20by%205.3%20years.%20In%20North%20India%2C%20this%20pollution%20is%20even%20more%2