2%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Has%20the%20BRICS%20Meeting%20in%20Johannesburg%20Eclipsed%20the%20Upcoming%20G20%20Show%20in%20Delhi%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30154118%2FIMG_0555.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHas%20the%20BRICS%20meeting%20in%20Johannesburg%20eclipsed%20the%20upcoming%20G20%20show%20in%20New%20Delhi%3F%20Yes%2C%20at%20least%20in%20articulating%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20(MTS)%2C%20particularly%20at%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%20(WTO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20MTS%20is%20being%20fractured%20into%20pieces%20and%20the%20WTO%20appears%20to%20be%20irreversibly%20atrophied%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FImages%2FCPV%2FDeclaration_2408.pdf%5C%22%3EJohannesburg%20II%20declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20expanded%20BRICS%20(Brazil%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20China%2C%20South%20Africa%20with%20six%20new%20members%20%E2%80%93%20Argentina%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20and%20United%20Arab%20Emirates)%20summit%20showed%20the%20mirror%20to%20the%20Northern%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20brought%20the%20central%20challenges%20facing%20the%20developing%20and%20least-developed%20countries%20in%20the%20MTS%20to%20the%20centerstage.%20It%20reiterates%20the%20long-pending%20concerns%20of%20the%20developing%20and%20the%20least-developed%20countries%20at%20the%20WTO.%20More%20importantly%2C%20it%20offers%20a%20comprehensive%20agenda%20for%20reforming%20the%20existing%20international%20financial%20institutions.%20As%20the%20global%20financial%20system%20based%20on%20the%20dollar%20gives%20way%20to%20international%20trading%20in%20other%20BRICS%20currencies%2C%20a%20paradigmatic%20shift%20is%20certainly%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELittle%20wonder%2C%20the%20Western%20media%2C%20including%20the%20much-respected%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fdc227378-6e08-46bd-abc0-77344b1cac28%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20gripped%20with%20a%20palpable%20fear%20that%20the%20BRICS%20project%20could%20change%20the%20international%20economic%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sharp%20contrast%2C%20while%20the%20G20%20leaders%E2%80%99%20meeting%20is%20scheduled%20to%20commence%20on%20September%209%2C%20the%20G20%20Trade%20and%20Investment%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Meeting%20(TIMM)%2C%20which%20concluded%20under%20the%20Indian%20presidency%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20royal%20Rambagh%20Palace%20of%20Jaipur%20rajas%20on%20August%2025%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20failed%20to%20live%20up%20to%20its%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20is%20understandable%20that%20there%20is%20no%20communique%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20meeting%20because%20of%20the%20proposed%20language%20on%20the%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20the%20Outcome%20Document%20and%20the%20chair%E2%80%99s%20summary%20of%20the%20G20%20TIMM%20appear%20to%20have%20elevated%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20dominant%20Northern%20countries%20such%20as%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20Japan%20and%20Canada%20among%20others%20in%20the%20global%20trading%20system%20and%20also%20their%20WTO%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorse%20still%2C%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20are%20articulated%20in%20anaemic%20language%20with%20limited%20or%20no%20implications%2C%20while%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20TIMM%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20commerce%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%2C%20claimed%20success%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgroundbreaking%E2%80%9D%20consensus%20at%20the%20concluding%20press%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETale%20of%20two%20narratives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cursory%20glance%20at%20the%20two%20narratives%20%E2%80%93%20one%20issued%20in%20Johannesburg%20and%20the%20other%20at%20the%20Jaipur%20meeting%20%E2%80%93%20reveals%20why%20the%20Johannesburg%20II%20declaration%20represents%20a%20watershed%20moment%20for%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20a%20mere%20continuation%20of%20the%20previous%20anodyne%20outcomes%20in%20the%20G20%20TIMM%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20ought%20to%20have%20recognised%20the%20asymmetrical%20framework%20underlying%20the%20G20%20before%20declaring%20itself%20as%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20includes%2019%20industrialised%20and%20several%20developing%20countries%3A%20Argentina%2C%20Australia%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Canada%2C%20China%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Italy%2C%20Japan%2C%20Republic%20of%20Korea%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Russia%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Turkey%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20establishment%20in%20the%20shadows%20of%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20in%20Washington%20in%202008%2C%20successive%20G20%20meetings%20merely%20reinforced%20the%20Northern%20trade%20and%20finance%20agenda%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20dominant%20international%20institutions%20like%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20the%20WTO%2C%20and%20the%20Paris-based%20OECD%20(Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Development).%20Of%20course%2C%20routinely%20the%20United%20Nations%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20and%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement%20were%20also%20reinforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%20seems%20ready%20to%20violate%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20agreement%20by%20unilaterally%20announcing%20punitive%20protectionist%20measures%20like%20the%20carbon%20border%20taxes.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20appears%20each%20G20%20meeting%20has%20become%20an%20event%20for%20record-keeping%20and%20further%20embracing%20narratives%20largely%20set%20by%20the%20US%20and%20other%20industrialised%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20easy%20to%20make%20pronouncements%20about%20the%20need%20to%20address%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20poor%20people%20and%20communities%2C%20as%20India%20did%20in%20the%20closed-door%20room%20meeting%20on%20August%2024%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20different%20struggle%20to%20reflect%20these%20concerns%20in%20the%20final%20language%20of%20the%20TIMM%20outcome%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDivergent%20concerns%20for%20Global%20South%20at%20Johannesburg%20and%20Jaipur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20Johannesburg%20II%20declaration%20on%20trade%2C%20the%20language%20is%20robust%20and%20it%20forcefully%20represents%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%20Consider%20paragraph%20eight%20which%20%E2%80%9Creaffirms%E2%80%9D%20support%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20open%2C%20transparent%2C%20fair%2C%20predictable%2C%20inclusive%2C%20equitable%2C%20non-discriminatory%2C%20and%20rules-based%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20with%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%20(WTO)%20at%20its%20core%2C%20with%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment%20(S%26amp%3BDT)%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20Least%20Developed%20Countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20the%20same%20language%20figures%20in%20the%20G20%20TIMM%2C%20except%20for%20one%20vital%20difference%20that%20reinforces%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20on%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment.%20The%20G20%20TIMM%20document%20reaffirmed%20%E2%80%9Ca%20rules-based%2C%20non-discriminatory%2C%20fair%2C%20open%2C%20inclusive%2C%20equitable%2C%20sustainable%20and%20transparent%20multilateral%20trading%20system%2C%20with%20the%20WTO%20at%20its%20core%2C%20is%20indispensable%20to%20advancing%20our%20shared%20objectives%20of%20inclusive%20growth%2C%20innovation%2C%20job%20creation%20and%20sustainable%20development.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Indian%20presidency%20of%20G20%2C%20one%20would%20have%20expected%20at%20least%20strong%20language%20on%20the%20continuation%20of%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment%20to%20reinforce%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20developing%20and%20least-developed%20countries.%20Sadly%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20excluded%20from%20the%20TIMM%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20strengthening%20the%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment%20in%20the%20WTO%20rulebook%2C%20as%20demanded%20by%20more%20than%2090%20developing%20countries%2C%20the%20BRICS%20declaration%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9Cconcrete%20deliverables%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20upcoming%2013th%20ministerial%20conference%20of%20the%20WTO%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20call%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20a%20fully%20and%20well-functioning%20two-tier%20binding%20WTO%20dispute%20settlement%20system%20accessible%20to%20all%20members%20by%202024%2C%20and%20the%20selection%20of%20new%20Appellate%20Body%20Members%20without%20further%20delay%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20BRICS%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20which%20has%20constantly%20called%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20two-stage%20dispute%20settlement%20system%2C%20seemed%20unable%20to%20include%20strong%20language%20on%20this%20vital%20issue%20in%20the%20face%20of%20opposition%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20the%20TIMM%20merely%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20note%20the%20ongoing%20discussions%20on%20Dispute%20Settlement%20reform%20and%20remain%20committed%20to%20conducting%20discussions%20with%20a%20view%20to%20having%20a%20fully%20and%20well-functioning%20Dispute%20Settlement%20System%2C%20accessible%20to%20all%20members%2C%20by%202024.%E2%80%9D%20Effectively%2C%20the%20above%20G20%20language%20does%20not%20guarantee%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20two-tier%20system%20or%20the%20Appellate%20Body.%20Without%20a%20binding%20two-tier%20system%20undergirding%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20enforcement%20function%2C%20the%20WTO%20will%20be%20run%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%98might%20is%20right%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20the%20US%20wants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20the%20BRICS%20declaration%2C%20in%20paragraph%20nine%2C%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20to%20make%20progress%20towards%20the%20achievement%20of%20a%20fair%20and%20market-oriented%20agricultural%20trading%20system%2C%20ending%20hunger%2C%20achieving%20food%20security%20and%20improved%20nutrition%2C%20promoting%20sustainable%20agriculture%20and%20food%20systems%2C%20and%20implement%20resilient%20agricultural%20practices%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20the%20need%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdeliver%20on%20agriculture%20reform%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20mandate%20in%20Article%2020%20of%20the%20Agreement%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20while%20recognizing%20the%20importance%20of%20respecting%20the%20mandates%20with%20regards%20to%20a%20Permanent%20Solution%20on%20Public%20Stockholding%20(PSH)%20for%20food%20security%20purposes%20and%20special%20safeguard%20mechanism%20(SSM)%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20LDCs%2C%20in%20their%20respective%20negotiating%20contexts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20Johannesburg%20declaration%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CBRICS%20members%20are%20also%20concerned%20with%20trade-restrictive%20measures%20which%20are%20inconsistent%20with%20WTO%20rules%2C%20including%20unilateral%20illegal%20measures%20such%20as%20sanctions%2C%20that%20affect%20agricultural%20trade.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20G20%20TIMM%20meeting%20of%20senior%20officials%20a%20day%20before%20the%20actual%20ministerial%20meeting%2C%20the%20US%20opposed%20any%20language%20based%20on%20WTO-inconsistent%20measures.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20unsurprising%20that%20India%2C%20the%20much-touted%20champion%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20seemed%20unable%20to%20stop%20the%20US%20from%20inserting%20language%20that%20is%20inimical%20to%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrade%20and%20environment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20on%20which%20the%20BRICS%20declaration%20seemed%20more%20credible%20and%20relevant%20for%20the%20developing%20countries%20is%20on%20trade%20and%20environment.%20It%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20oppose%20trade%20barriers%20including%20those%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20tackling%20climate-change%20imposed%20by%20certain%20developed%20countries%20(as%20well%20as%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20Director-General%20Ms%20Ngozi%20Okonjo-Iweala%20who%20has%20currently%20tasked%20the%20WTO%20Secretariat%20to%20prepare%20a%20framework%20for%20carbon-pricing%20without%20any%20ministerial%20mandate)%20and%20reiterate%20our%20commitment%20to%20enhancing%20coordination%20on%20these%20issues.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20underlines%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmeasures%20taken%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change%20and%20biodiversity%20loss%20must%20be%20WTO-consistent%20and%20must%20not%20constitute%20a%20means%20of%20arbitrary%20or%20unjustifiable%20discrimination%20or%20a%20disguised%20restriction%20on%20international%20trade%20and%20should%20not%20create%20unnecessary%20obstacles%20to%20international%20trade.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20such%20measure%20must%20be%20guided%20by%20the%20principle%20of%20common%20but%20differentiated%20responsibilities%20and%20respective%20capabilities%20(CBDR-RC)%2C%20in%20the%20light%20of%20different%20national%20circumstances%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20BRICS%20declaration%20maintained.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20express%20our%20concern%20at%20any%20WTO%20inconsistent%20discriminatory%20measure%20that%20will%20distort%20international%20trade%2C%20risk%20new%20trade%20barriers%2C%20and%20shift%20the%20burden%20of%20addressing%20climate%20change%20and%20biodiversity%20loss%20to%20BRICS%20members%20and%20developing%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20the%20G20%20TIMM%20Jaipur%20Outcome%20Document%2C%20in%20paragraph%20nine%2C%20merely%20recalls%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctrade%20and%20environment%20policies%20should%20be%20mutually%20supportive%2C%20consistent%20with%20WTO%20and%20multilateral%20environmental%20agreements.%20We%20further%20acknowledge%20the%20essential%20role%20of%20multilateral%20cooperation%20to%20effectively%20address%20common%20environmental%20and%20sustainable%20development%20challenges.%20We%20will%20engage%20in%20further%20discussions%20on%20trade%20and%20sustainability.%E2%80%9D%20Surely%2C%20this%20diluted%20language%20does%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20Southern%20countries%20in%20the%20coming%20days%20and%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20it%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20G20%20is%20a%20grouping%20of%20major%20industrialised%20countries%20with%20limited%20say%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20unlike%20the%20BRICS%2C%20but%20if%20India%20truly%20represents%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20then%20it%20should%20have%20pushed%20for%20stronger%20language%20on%20key%20issues%20of%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fravi-kanth-devarakonda%5C%22%3ERavi%20Kanth%20Devarakonda%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693395046000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30154118%2FIMG_0555.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fhas-the-brics-meeting-in-johannesburg-eclipsed-the-upcoming-g20-show-in-delhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BRICS%20summit%20brought%20the%20central%20challenges%20facing%20the%20developing%20and%20least-developed%20countries%20in%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20to%20the%20centerstage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fhas-the-brics-meeting-in-johannesburg-eclipsed-the-upcoming-g20-show-in-delhi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%2